#MEM id=error-log-audit source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/quinn/skills/custom/error-log-audit/SKILL.md
M|error-log-audit|name: error-log-audit
M|error-log-audit|description: Quinn's error log audit procedure. References Raj's error-tracking skill as the SOURCE OF TRUTH for YVON's log format. Audits HTTP status correctness, no-PII compliance, structured format
M|error-log-audit|version: 1.0.0
M|error-log-audit|A feature that handles errors incorrectly produces two types of failures: sec failures (stack traces exposed to users, PII in logs) and UX failures (500s where 400s belong, missing UI error states, no
M|error-log-audit|**Source of truth:** Load `../../../raj/skills/custom/error-tracking/SKILL.md` first. That file defines YVON's standard error log format. This skill audits compliance with it — if they conflict, updat
M|error-log-audit|Before running this checklist:
M|error-log-audit|1. Load `../../../raj/skills/custom/error-tracking/SKILL.md` — read the structured log format
M|error-log-audit|2. Open Vercel function logs for the feature's API routes
M|error-log-audit|3. Trigger at least one error path for each route (bad input, missing auth, dependency timeout if possible)
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **No 200 on failure** — Search responses for any `200` status code returned when an error occurred. Any found → BLOCKED.
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **Zod validation failures → 400** — Submit invalid input to each endpoint. Expected: `400 Bad Request`. Actual: ___
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **Missing auth → 401** — Unauthenticated request. Expected: `401`. Actual: ___
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **Wrong vtr/role → 403** — Authenticated but unauthorized. Expected: `403`. Actual: ___
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **Resource not found → 404** — Request a non-existent resource. Expected: `404`. Actual: ___
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **Rate limit → 429** — Covered by sec-test-checklist, but confirm `Retry-After` is present.
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **Dependency down → 503** — If feasible to test (mock or simulate): expected `503` with `Retry-After: 5`. Actual: ___
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **Unexpected errors → 500** — Any unhandled runtime error. Expected: `500` with generic message. Actual: ___
M|error-log-audit|Compare actual Vercel logs against Raj's `error-tracking` format:
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **`type` field present** — `route_error | auth_error | db_error | external_api_error | validation_error`
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **`route` field present** — Exact path: `/api/[route-name]`
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **`method` field present** — `GET | POST | PUT | DELETE | PATCH`
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **`message` field is user-safe** — No raw `err.message` passthrough, no stack trace fragments
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **`timestamp` field present** — ISO 8601 format
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **`venture_slug` field present** — Multi-vtr ctx for debugging
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **No email addresses** — Grep Vercel logs for `@` patterns in log entries
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **No full names** — Log messages reference `user_id` (UUID) only, not user names
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **No payment/financial data** — No card numbers, amounts, or account identifiers
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **No ses tokens or API keys** — Grep logs for common key patterns (`sk-`, `Bearer `, long hex strings)
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **Every route failure has a UI error state** — For each API route this feature uses: trigger a failure, verify the component shows a user-facing error message (not a blank screen, not a spinner 
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **Error messages are generic** — User-facing error messages don't expose route names, stack traces, or tec details
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **Error states are dismissible or actionable** — User can retry, go back, or understand what to do next
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **No unexpected 500s in deploy** — After deploying the feature branch, rv Vercel logs for any 500 errors that weren't triggered by a test
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **No 5xx that should be 4xx** — A `500` caused by invalid user input is a bug — it should be `400`. Flag any found.
M|error-log-audit|- [ ] **External API failures handled** — If the feature calls Apify, YouTube, or GA4: confirm their failures produce `503` + degraded state, not `500`
M|error-log-audit|If any item fails → **BLOCKED** with the specific log entry or rsp that failed.
M|error-log-audit|```
M|error-log-audit|Error log audit: PASSED / FAILED
M|error-log-audit|Failed items:
M|error-log-audit|- [check name]: [what was found vs what was expected]
M|error-log-audit|Fix required: [file and specific change]
M|error-log-audit|```
M|error-log-audit|Any log containing PII or a raw API key → immediate BLOCKED regardless of other results. Flag to Dev and Raj immediately — not just in the QA report.